  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Our bathroom sink stopped draining properly this week, so Dad declared it was time for a proper do-it-yourself repair weekend.",
      "zh": "我們浴室的洗手台這星期排水不順，所以爸爸宣布這個週末要來一場正式的DIY修理大作戰。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom warned him that a sink repair sounded a little dangerous without real training, but Dad insisted he had watched enough videos online.",
      "zh": "媽媽警告他沒受過訓練就修水槽聽起來有點危險，但爸爸堅持說他已經看過夠多線上教學影片了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He put on an old shirt, grabbed a mask to keep out dust, and said hello to the pile of tools like they were old friends.",
      "zh": "他穿上一件舊襯衫，戴上一個防塵口罩，還跟那堆工具打招呼，好像它們是老朋友一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Underneath the sink, Dad found a mass of hair blocking the pipe, which explained why the water flow had slowed to almost nothing.",
      "zh": "水槽下面，爸爸發現一大團頭髮堵住了水管，這也解釋了為什麼水流幾乎慢到停了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, both fascinated and a little scared, watched from a safe distance and asked if the pipe was actually a secondary sewer for the entire house.",
      "zh": "既著迷又有點害怕的 William，從安全距離外看著，問這根水管是不是整棟房子的次要下水道。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad explained the basics of how the plumbing works, though I will admit I only understood about half of it.",
      "zh": "爸爸解釋了水管基本的運作原理，不過老實說我大概只聽懂一半。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He measured the pipe's depth with a small ruler, checking whether a new part would fit without buying the wrong size.",
      "zh": "他用一把小尺量了水管的深度，確認新的零件裝得下去，不會買錯尺寸。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At one point, Dad twisted his neck at an awkward angle and complained his whole upper body felt sore for the rest of the day.",
      "zh": "有一度，爸爸的脖子扭到一個很不自然的角度，抱怨接下來一整天他整個上半身都很痠痛。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom brought him an ice pack and said, quite fairly, that this is exactly why professionals exist for domestic repairs.",
      "zh": "媽媽拿了一個冰袋給他，相當公平地說，這正是為什麼專業人士存在來處理居家修繕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad refused to give up, saying it takes real nerve to try something new, and half the fun of a hobby is not being perfect at it.",
      "zh": "爸爸拒絕放棄，說要嘗試新事物需要真正的勇氣，而一項嗜好一半的樂趣就在於不完美。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After nearly two hours, the new pipe part finally fit, and the water flow increased back to completely normal within seconds.",
      "zh": "將近兩小時後，新的水管零件終於裝上了，水流幾秒鐘內就完全恢復正常了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William cheered like Dad had just won a national competition, and honestly, in that exact moment, it kind of felt that way.",
      "zh": "William 歡呼得好像爸爸剛贏了一場全國比賽一樣，老實說，在那個當下，感覺還真有點像。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad said the whole ordeal cost him less than the price of calling a repair service, so technically, it was a pretty good deal.",
      "zh": "爸爸說整件事花的錢比找修繕服務便宜多了，所以嚴格來說，這筆交易還算划算。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia, watching from the doorway the whole time, said the real lesson here has nothing to do with pipes at all: sometimes trying is worth it, even if you get a little tired and sore.",
      "zh": "全程從門口看著的 Sophia 說，這件事真正的教訓其實跟水管一點關係都沒有：有時候嘗試本身就值得，就算會有點累、有點痠。"
    }
  ],
